On Dec 1, 2024, at 2:38 PM, Taco Taco <info@eattaco.ca> wrote:

Hi Lauren,

I just sent an updated contract for the 13th!

For food, we can offer light appetizers for $6 per person. This includes loaded nachos, jalapeno poppers, fries and bruschetta. If you want to do two tacos+appetizers per person, we can do it for $16 per person. You can choose between 4-6 tacos and apps and can see the full menu here: eattaco.ca/menu. If you want a full plated buffet catering, it would be $30 per person. I've attached the plated buffet menu for reference. For all options, we serve all food on long tables and people grab plates to grab whatever they like.

If you'd like to provide drinks for your guests, you can purchase drink tickets at $8 each + tax & gratuity which covers all our drinks except for the cocktails. It's hard to add cocktails since it's $14-$16 each, Or, you can set a budget for open bar and people can order from the open bar until that limit is reached. This may be better if you want to include cocktails. 

TacoTaco Events Team
(647) 692-4768 | info@eattaco.ca 
eattaco.ca

No worries! Last year we had an overwhelming response and lots more people attended that we initially anticipated - so I think we ended up being in both the front section of the venue and the back. I like the Friday the 13th spot. Nice celebratory way to wind up the week!

Maybe it’s good to confirm a few of the details.

Headcount: 100 (max)
Time: 6-8PM
Budget: $2.5k (pre-tax)
Drink tickets: 1 per head, available to redeem for mocktail, cocktail, bar rail, soft drink, etc. (we can discuss a price cap and pay by consumption?)

For F&B, I’m imagining light bites and quantity will be largely determined by out budget.

How does all of this sound?

Hi Lauren,

I just sent an updated contract for the 13th!

For food, we can offer light appetizers for $6 per person. This includes loaded nachos, jalapeno poppers, fries and bruschetta. If you want to do two tacos+appetizers per person, we can do it for $16 per person. You can choose between 4-6 tacos and apps and can see the full menu here: eattaco.ca/menu. If you want a full plated buffet catering, it would be $30 per person. I've attached the plated buffet menu for reference. For all options, we serve all food on long tables and people grab plates to grab whatever they like.

If you'd like to provide drinks for your guests, you can purchase drink tickets at $8 each + tax & gratuity which covers all our drinks except for the cocktails. It's hard to add cocktails since it's $14-$16 each, Or, you can set a budget for open bar and people can order from the open bar until that limit is reached. This may be better if you want to include cocktails.

Good afternoon!

I design and deliver alumni events at UofT for the Faculty of Information alumni community.

We held our winter holiday event at Taco Taco last year and had such an overwhelmingly positive response I’d love to explore holding it at your venue again this year. Would you have any availability for the week of Dec 13?

Thank you!
Lauren

On Nov 13, 2023, at 5:28 PM, info@eattaco.ca wrote:

﻿

Sounds good! Let me draft up a contract. For the catering, can you let me know about 24 hours in advance your updated estimate for attendance? And then we’ll serve and charge accordingly. You might want to go with a lower amount, and then we can always add more food the night of the event if necessary.

 

TacoTaco Events Team

319 Augusta Ave

eattaco.ca/events

From: Lauren Kilgour <kilgour.lauren@gmail.com>
Sent: Monday, November 13, 2023 4:51 PM
To: info@eattaco.ca
Subject: Re: New Event Inquiry

 

Wonderful! With that in mind, I’d be thrilled to go ahead and confirm the booking for the Dining Room 6-8PM on November 30.

 

Related to the menu, I can see that the fees are laid out as a per head fee. Given that our event has flexible attendance, I wonder how we might move forward with planning this element of our event.

 

For past events, I have put in an order ahead of time and then we’ve also built in the option to place orders on the night-of depending on how many attendees we have and how quickly the food and beverages are finished.

 

What would make the most sense in your eyes? We anticipate about 30-50 attendees and will have need for some vegan, vegetarian, gluten-free, halal, kosher, etc. dietary requirements.

 

Would it be possible to design a menu and catering plan around these elements?

 

Thanks very much for confirming our booking and please do let me know what information I can provide on our side!

 

Best,

Lauren

text:
I'd love to hear your favourite puns when we meet 🤭
I won't be around that area until the event - I'm actually on the east end
and the next couple weeks are crazy busy. But I'm going out with some
friends on the 13th, I'll try to bring them to Kensington if you're around!

My number: 437-265-2503
Timeframe: 6-9pm, if it's okay we'd come by earlier for any setup needs.
Let me know how strict you're on time, we post the event until 9pm usually
but it always takes considerable effort to kick people out.

Sounds good re:contract and deposit, send me the details.

For food we will take your $6 package, but do you have more vegan options?
We can do a mix (I love a jalapeno popper 🤤) but we have a lot of
vegetarian and vegans in the crowd.
We will do the drink tickets as you suggested, that's perfect. Ill give you
a head count closer to the date!

Questions - I assume you have a mic from the karaoke set that we could use?
And do you use reusable dishes and cutlery? It would be preferred to
anything disposable.

Have a great weekend!

Becky Park-Romanovsky
Climate North Co-Founder

I'd love to hear your favourite puns when we meet 🤭
I won't be around that area until the event - I'm actually on the east end and the next couple weeks are crazy busy. But I'm going out with some friends on the 13th, I'll try to bring them to Kensington if you're around!

My number: 437-265-2503
Timeframe: 6-9pm, if it's okay we'd come by earlier for any setup needs. Let me know how strict you're on time, we post the event until 9pm usually but it always takes considerable effort to kick people out.

Sounds good re:contract and deposit, send me the details.

For food we will take your $6 package, but do you have more vegan options? We can do a mix (I love a jalapeno popper 🤤) but we have a lot of vegetarian and vegans in the crowd. 
We will do the drink tickets as you suggested, that's perfect. Ill give you a head count closer to the date! 

Questions - I assume you have a mic from the karaoke set that we could use? 
And do you use reusable dishes and cutlery? It would be preferred to anything disposable. 

Have a great weekend! 

Becky Park-Romanovsky
Climate North Co-Founder

On Fri, Nov 29, 2024, 15:49 Taco Taco <info@eattaco.ca> wrote:
Haha the amount of puns we can make here at Tacotaco is unbelievable you wouldn't even know. I'll try to come out for the 16th, but if you want to catch up beforehand let me know if you want to come to the restaurant and I'll make time to swing by! We'll give you some tacos on the house :) 

Can I get your phone number and timeframe you want to have the event? I can have a contract created for you to review, you just have to accept it. We do ask for a deposit, in this case I can ask for $200 and it's fully refundable assuming minimum spend is hit. 

For food, we can offer light appetizers for $6 per person. This includes loaded nachos, jalapeno poppers, fries and bruschetta. If you want to do two tacos+appetizers per person, we can do it for $16 per person. You can choose between 4-6 tacos and apps and can see the full menu here: eattaco.ca/menu. If you want a full plated buffet catering, it would be $30 per person. I've attached the plated buffet menu for reference. For all options, we serve all food on long tables and people grab plates to grab whatever they like.

If you'd like to provide drinks for your guests, you can purchase drink tickets at $8 each + tax & gratuity which covers all our drinks except for the cocktails, that'll likely be the most effective way to go about it!

TacoTaco Events Team
(647) 692-4768 | info@eattaco.ca 
eattaco.ca

NO WAY!! Liem! How cool is that, I had no idea you were in Toronto. We should definitely catch up, are you there on Sunday? I'll be around.

Since it's you, full transparency we got a better price from Collective Arts. Any chance there is flexibility with the rate? Would love to support your business! 

To answer your question, we are anticipating around 40 people. To be honest our events usually have 60-70 attendees but they're presentation/panel style. This "fun" type of event is a first for us, so I'm being conservative just in case. 

Let me know 😊

Becky
